main event: A UFO sighting was reported in Walton, New York on April 22, 1965, with two witnesses observing a single object.
interesting points: The sighting lasted for approximately 10 minutes., The report was classified as a close contact with an unidentified flying object., The conclusion of the investigation was that the object had landed and was deemed 'unreal.', No physical evidence or photographs were available to support the sighting., A follow-up letter referenced a meteor sighting occurring in the same region at the same time.
witness description: The witnesses reported seeing a round red lighted object that appeared to be hovering.
